-- Apple Introduces iBook 2 to Help Boost IPad in Schools
-- B y   A d a m   S a t a r i a n o
-- 2012-01-19T15:20:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/apple-introduces-digital-textbook-product-to-boost-ipad-use-in-schools.html
Apple Inc. (AAPL) , the world’s largest
technology company, introduced a new product to make digital
versions of textbooks available on the iPad.  The new service is called “iBooks 2” and is intended to
help make textbooks more interactive and searchable,  Phil
Schiller , Apple’s senior vice president of product marketing,
said today at an announcement in  New York . More than 1.5 million
iPads are being used for educational purposes, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
